      <summary>
        <versionCode>00</versionCode>
        <actionDate>2025-01-21</actionDate>
        <actionDesc>Introduced in House</actionDesc>
        <updateDate>2025-04-14T18:03:55Z</updateDate>
        <cdata>
          <text>&lt;p&gt;This bill expands the definition of a qualifying child to include a stillborn child for purposes of the child tax credit. (Under current law, taxpayers may claim a tax credit of up $2,000 for each qualifying child.)&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Under the bill, a stillborn child is an unborn child (1) carried in the womb for a gestational period of 20 weeks or more, and (2) delivered after the spontaneous intrauterine fetal demise of the child.&lt;/p&gt;</text>
        </cdata>
      </summary>
    </summaries>
    <title>To amend the Internal Revenue Code of 1986 to allow the child tax credit with respect to stillbirths.</title>
